The family of Peter Mayhew, who played Chewbecca in the original Star Wars franchise, announced his death on Twitter on Thursday. He was 74. Mayhew died in his North Texas home surrounded by his family, the statement on Twitter said. He is survived by his wife, Angie Mayhew, and their three children. The family will hold a funeral on 29 June and in early December 2019, there will be a memorial for fans of Chewbecca in Los Angeles at EmpireConLA. The family suggested fans and loved ones donate to Mayhew’s foundation in lieu of flowers or gifts. William Shatner, who played Captain Kirk in Star Trek, expressed his condolences on Twitter, remembering the times he saw the actor at conventions over the years. More details soon…